== Description ==
[[File:Stabilizer2.jpg|thumb|A Destabilizer in [[M.E.G.|MEG]] custody (temporarily).|321x321px]]
'''Object 99''', aka "Destabilizer", is an anomalous object resembling a modified pink & red toy walkie talkie presumably designed for children. Despite this object's small size and unassuming appearance, it is one of the most useful and mysterious items in the Backrooms. It is unknown whether '''Object 99''' is singular, as walkie talkies usually come in pairs, but there have never been reports of contact with '''Object 99''' in overlapping time periods, so it is impossible to say for sure.

On its front, the device has 6 black ovular buttons in a semicircle pattern around a green number display, and 3 other buttons below them. At the bottom, a speaker is present for relaying audio. An antenna and light are present at the top. The back side of the object has a small panel that can be removed to view its interior. 

Though not visible from the outside, this object has undergone extreme internal circuitry modifications (including the removal of any identifiable power source), which are likely the cause of its anomalous properties (see '''Usage'''). The delicate internal machinery has so far dissuaded anyone from attempting to dissect it for fear of breaking it.

== Usage ==
'''Object 99'''<nowiki/>'s primary usage and/or purpose appears to be its ability to manipulate and control [[Phenomenon 1-A|no-clipping]] at any time simply by pressing its buttons in a certain order. For example, this process can allow wanderers to broadcast signals to any intact radio in a specific level, and even induce instability at the user's current location by changing an onscreen value to anything negative, thus causing a [[Phenomenon 1-A|'''no-clip''']]. The device is also theoretically capable of stabilizing otherwise untraversable terrain due to the fact that the aforementioned button can receive inputs above zero, though this has yet to be proven.

'''Object 99''' likely has other additional useful properties which have yet to be studied. However, prolonged experimentation has been delayed by the fact that '''Object 99''' always [[Phenomenon 1-A|'''no-clips''']] again less than 24 hours after being first discovered- whether intentional or by malfunction is unknown, though the latter seems more likely. Attempts to both contain and/or replicate the device have always failed. It is highly recommended not to approach '''Object 99''' or keep it on one's person for an extended period of time, as you may be caught in its subsequent vanishing. The device has so far been responsible for 3 reported disappearances.

== Location ==
Due to '''Object 99'''<nowiki/>'s elusive nature, a single location is impossible to pinpoint, and its origin is equally as mysterious. However, it has been reportedly discovered at least once in the following levels:

* [[Level 4|'''Level 4''']]
* [[Level 1|'''Level 1''']]
* [[Level 11|'''Level 11''']]
* [[The Hub|'''The Hub''']]
* [[Level 154|'''Level 154''']]
* [[Level 305|'''Level 305''']]
* [[Level 655|'''Level 655''']]

== Discovery ==
'''Object 99''' was first reported in 2019 as an anomalous walkie-talkie which a wanderer had used to '''[[Phenomenon 1-A|no-clip]]''' through several '''[[Level List|levels]]''' before losing track of. The device remained uncatalogued for several years despite multiple similar reports until the '''[[M.E.G.|MEG]]''' secured it for testing in 2023. It has since been recaptured by operatives 3 times, with each yielding more information about the object's nature and use. If you believe you are in possession of '''Object 99''', please bring it to the nearest '''[[M.E.G.|MEG]]''' outpost as soon as possible. 

